This paper deals with a stochastic submodular maximization problem with dependent items subject to packing constraints such as matroid and knapsack constraints. The problem involves selecting a group of items adaptively so as to maximize the expected utility. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information theory (cs.IT), and game theory (cs.GT).
